{"title_page": "State epidemiologist (Sweden)", "text_new": "{{Infobox official post\n| post                     = State epidemiologist\n| body                     = [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]]\n| native_name              = {{lang|sv|Statsepidemiolog}}\n| insignia                 = \n| insigniasize             = \n| insigniacaption          = \n| flag                     = Flag of Sweden.svg\n| flagsize                 = 150px\n| flagborder               = yes\n| flagcaption              = [[Sweden]]\n| image                    = \n| imagesize                = \n| alt                      = \n| incumbent                = [[Anders Tegnell]]\n| acting                   = \n| incumbentsince           = 2013\n| department               = Department of Public Health Analysis and Data Management\n| style                    = \n| type                     = \n| status                   = \n| abbreviation             = \n| member_of                = \n| reports_to               = Johan Carlsson ([[director general]])\n| residence                = \n| seat                     = [[Solna]], [[Stockholm County]]\n| nominator                = \n| appointer                = \n| appointer_qualified      = \n| termlength               = \n| termlength_qualified     = \n| constituting_instrument  = \n| precursor                = [[Annika Linde]]\n| formation                = [[1955]]\n| first                    = Bo Zetterberg\n| last                     = \n| abolished                = \n| succession               = Fifth\n| unofficial_names         = \n| deputy                   = \n| salary                   = \n| website                  = \n}}\nThe '''state epidemiologist''', or the '''chief epidemiologist''' (plural: ''state epidemiologists or chief epidemiologists'') is a [[Swedish]] civil servant.  Initially, the state epidemiologist was the head of the epidemiology department at the State Bacteriological Laboratory at the time of its establishment in 1955.<ref>{{bokref|title=Statens Bakteriologiska Laboratorium|year=1993|publisher=Statens Bakteriologiska Laboratorium|page=35|author=Margareta B\u00f6ttiger|editor=Carin Winter|location=Solna/Stockholm|chapter=Epidemiologin}}</ref> In 1993, the post was transferred to the newly founded agency Institute for Communicable Disease Control. After the Institute was merged with [[Public Health Agency of Sweden#History|Swedish National Institute of Public Health]] in 2014, the post became part of the new agency [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Avdelningen f\u00f6r epidemiologi och utv\u00e4rdering|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/om-folkhalsomyndigheten/organisation/avdelningar-och-enheter/epidemiologi-utvardering/|publisher=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|accessdate=10 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==List of Swedish state epidemiologists==\n* 1956\u20131976: Bo Zetterberg\n* 1976\u20131993: Margareta B\u00f6ttiger\n* 1995\u20132005: Johan Giesecke\n* 2005\u20132013: [[Annika Linde]]\n* 2013\u2013:     [[Anders Tegnell]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/ Public Health Agency of Sweden]\n\n[[Category:Government agencies of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organizations based in Sweden]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox official post\n| post                     = State epidemiologist\n| body                     = [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]]\n| native_name              = {{lang|sv|Statsepidemiolog}}\n| insignia                 = \n| insigniasize             = \n| insigniacaption          = \n| flag                     = Flag of Sweden.svg\n| flagsize                 = 150px\n| flagborder               = yes\n| flagcaption              = [[Sweden]]\n| image                    = \n| imagesize                = \n| alt                      = \n| incumbent                = [[Anders Tegnell]]\n| acting                   = \n| incumbentsince           = 2013\n| department               = Department of Public Health Analysis and Data Management\n| style                    = \n| type                     = \n| status                   = \n| abbreviation             = \n| member_of                = \n| reports_to               = Johan Carlsson ([[director general]])\n| residence                = \n| seat                     = [[Solna]], [[Stockholm County]]\n| nominator                = \n| appointer                = \n| appointer_qualified      = \n| termlength               = \n| termlength_qualified     = \n| constituting_instrument  = \n| precursor                = [[Annika Linde]]\n| formation                = [[1955]]\n| first                    = Bo Zetterberg\n| last                     = \n| abolished                = \n| succession               = Fifth\n| unofficial_names         = \n| deputy                   = \n| salary                   = \n| website                  = \n}}\nThe '''state epidemiologist''', or the '''chief epidemiologist''' (plural: ''state epidemiologists or chief epidemiologists'') is a [[Swedish]] civil servant.  Initially, the state epidemiologist was the head of the epidemiology department at the State Bacteriological Laboratory at the time of its establishment in 1955.<ref>{{bokref|title=Statens Bakteriologiska Laboratorium|year=1993|publisher=Statens Bakteriologiska Laboratorium|page=35|author=Margareta B\u00f6ttiger|editor=Carin Winter|location=Solna/Stockholm|chapter=Epidemiologin}}</ref> In 1993, the post was transferred to the newly founded agency Institute for Communicable Disease Control. After the Institute was merged with [[Public Health Agency of Sweden#History|Swedish National Institute of Public Health]] in 2014, the post became part of the new agency [[Public Health Agency of Sweden]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Avdelningen f\u00f6r epidemiologi och utv\u00e4rdering|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/om-folkhalsomyndigheten/organisation/avdelningar-och-enheter/epidemiologi-utvardering/|publisher=Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|accessdate=10 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==List of Swedish state epidemiologists==\n* 1956\u20131976: Bo Zetterberg\n* 1976\u20131993: Margareta B\u00f6ttiger\n* 1995\u20132005: Johan Giesecke\n* 2005\u20132013: [[Annika Linde]]\n* 2013\u2013:     [[Anders Tegnell]]\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/ Public Health Agency of Sweden]\n\n[[Category:Government agencies of Sweden]]\n[[Category:Medical and health organizations based in Sweden]]\n", "name_user": "Zanimum", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_epidemiologist_(Sweden)"}
